China’s Stocks Rally, Helping Shanghai Composite Index Erase Loss for Year

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-07-04T05:11:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/china-s-stocks-rally-helping-shanghai-composite-index-erase-loss-for-year.html
China’s stocks rallied, helping the
benchmark index to erase this year’s losses, as reports showing
a slowing economy prompted investors to speculate the central
bank will delay further increases in  interest rates .  The Shanghai Composite Index advanced as much as 1.9
percent, extending a two-week rally. The measure added 1.7
percent to 2,807.50 at 1:10 p.m.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  